Within the market segments, flexible packaging stands out as a key driver of growth due to its lightweight nature, cost-effectiveness, and recyclability. The flexibility and versatility of flexible packaging make it suitable for a wide range of products, from snacks and beverages to personal care items. Its ability to incorporate sustainable materials further enhances its appeal in the market. The food & beverage industry, being one of the largest consumers of packaging solutions, plays a significant role in driving market revenue. Brands in this sector are increasingly adopting sustainable packaging practices to align with consumer preferences and regulatory requirements, thereby creating opportunities for packaging providers offering eco-friendly solutions.

Among the material segments, plastics continue to dominate the Next Generation Packaging Market due to their cost-effectiveness, durability, and versatility. While there is growing scrutiny on the environmental impact of plastics, innovations in recyclable and biodegradable plastics are addressing these concerns and making them more sustainable options for packaging needs. Companies are investing in research and development to create bio-based plastics and improve the recyclability of plastic packaging, thus contributing to the overall sustainability goals of the industry.

